    <item>
      <title>About</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 25 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/about/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;reveal reveal--about-intro&#34;&gt;&#xA;  I’m a UX/UI Designer and Design Engineer based in Milan.&#xA;I’ve worked on digital products, games, and websites, with a strong focus on structure, systems, and complex user flows.&#xA;I’m less interested in visual polish and more in how things behave over time.&#xA;That’s where I do my best work.&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;accordion&#34; id=&#34;about-faq&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;&lt;details class=&#34;accordion__item reveal reveal--about-accordion&#34;  style=&#34;--i: 0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;summary class=&#34;accordion__summary&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;accordion__title&#34;&gt;What do you work on?&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;accordion__icon&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;svg aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; focusable=&#34;false&#34; width=&#34;%!s(int=16)px&#34; height=&#34;%!s(int=16)px&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 256 256&#34;&gt;&lt;rect width=&#34;256&#34; height=&#34;256&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;/&gt;&lt;rect x=&#34;40&#34; y=&#34;40&#34; width=&#34;176&#34; height=&#34;176&#34; rx=&#34;16&#34; opacity=&#34;0.2&#34;/&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;40&#34; y1=&#34;128&#34; x2=&#34;216&#34; y2=&#34;128&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;16&#34;/&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;128&#34; y1=&#34;40&#34; x2=&#34;128&#34; y2=&#34;216&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;16&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/summary&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;accordion__content&#34; role=&#34;region&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;accordion__content-inner&#34;&gt;&#xA;      I work on complex applications rather than showcase websites. I’m comfortable with products that have rules, states, and evolving requirements, where clarity comes from structure instead of visual emphasis.&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/details&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;details class=&#34;accordion__item reveal reveal--about-accordion&#34;  style=&#34;--i: 1;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;summary class=&#34;accordion__summary&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;accordion__title&#34;&gt;How do you approach design?&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;accordion__icon&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;svg aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; focusable=&#34;false&#34; width=&#34;%!s(int=16)px&#34; height=&#34;%!s(int=16)px&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 256 256&#34;&gt;&lt;rect width=&#34;256&#34; height=&#34;256&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;/&gt;&lt;rect x=&#34;40&#34; y=&#34;40&#34; width=&#34;176&#34; height=&#34;176&#34; rx=&#34;16&#34; opacity=&#34;0.2&#34;/&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;40&#34; y1=&#34;128&#34; x2=&#34;216&#34; y2=&#34;128&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;16&#34;/&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;128&#34; y1=&#34;40&#34; x2=&#34;128&#34; y2=&#34;216&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;16&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/summary&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;accordion__content&#34; role=&#34;region&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;accordion__content-inner&#34;&gt;&#xA;      I approach design as a system. I focus on relationships, constraints, and consistency, trying to understand how decisions affect the product as it grows.&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/details&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;details class=&#34;accordion__item reveal reveal--about-accordion&#34;  style=&#34;--i: 2;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;summary class=&#34;accordion__summary&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;accordion__title&#34;&gt;What are you not focused on?&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;accordion__icon&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;svg aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; focusable=&#34;false&#34; width=&#34;%!s(int=16)px&#34; height=&#34;%!s(int=16)px&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 256 256&#34;&gt;&lt;rect width=&#34;256&#34; height=&#34;256&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;/&gt;&lt;rect x=&#34;40&#34; y=&#34;40&#34; width=&#34;176&#34; height=&#34;176&#34; rx=&#34;16&#34; opacity=&#34;0.2&#34;/&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;40&#34; y1=&#34;128&#34; x2=&#34;216&#34; y2=&#34;128&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;16&#34;/&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;128&#34; y1=&#34;40&#34; x2=&#34;128&#34; y2=&#34;216&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;16&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/summary&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;accordion__content&#34; role=&#34;region&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;accordion__content-inner&#34;&gt;&#xA;      I don’t focus on graphic production such as illustrations, 3D modeling, animations, or posters. When a project needs that kind of visual work, I collaborate with graphic designers or other artists. My focus remains on interface design and system structure.&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/details&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;details class=&#34;accordion__item reveal reveal--about-accordion&#34;  style=&#34;--i: 3;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;summary class=&#34;accordion__summary&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;accordion__title&#34;&gt;Do you work close to code?&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;accordion__icon&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;svg aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; focusable=&#34;false&#34; width=&#34;%!s(int=16)px&#34; height=&#34;%!s(int=16)px&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 256 256&#34;&gt;&lt;rect width=&#34;256&#34; height=&#34;256&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;/&gt;&lt;rect x=&#34;40&#34; y=&#34;40&#34; width=&#34;176&#34; height=&#34;176&#34; rx=&#34;16&#34; opacity=&#34;0.2&#34;/&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;40&#34; y1=&#34;128&#34; x2=&#34;216&#34; y2=&#34;128&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;16&#34;/&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;128&#34; y1=&#34;40&#34; x2=&#34;128&#34; y2=&#34;216&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;16&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/summary&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;accordion__content&#34; role=&#34;region&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;accordion__content-inner&#34;&gt;&#xA;      Yes. I collaborate closely with developers and care about how interfaces are implemented, scaled, and maintained. This helps keep design decisions grounded in reality.&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/details&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;details class=&#34;accordion__item reveal reveal--about-accordion&#34;  style=&#34;--i: 4;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;summary class=&#34;accordion__summary&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;accordion__title&#34;&gt;What kind of projects are a good fit?&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;accordion__icon&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;svg aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; focusable=&#34;false&#34; width=&#34;%!s(int=16)px&#34; height=&#34;%!s(int=16)px&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 256 256&#34;&gt;&lt;rect width=&#34;256&#34; height=&#34;256&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;/&gt;&lt;rect x=&#34;40&#34; y=&#34;40&#34; width=&#34;176&#34; height=&#34;176&#34; rx=&#34;16&#34; opacity=&#34;0.2&#34;/&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;40&#34; y1=&#34;128&#34; x2=&#34;216&#34; y2=&#34;128&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;16&#34;/&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;128&#34; y1=&#34;40&#34; x2=&#34;128&#34; y2=&#34;216&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;16&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/summary&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;accordion__content&#34; role=&#34;region&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;accordion__content-inner&#34;&gt;&#xA;      Projects that deal with complexity seriously and value long term clarity. Applications, tools, and products that need to remain understandable as they evolve.&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/details&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>A data visualization project that goes beyond data</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/projects/the-weather-in-troms%C3%B8/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 21 Jan 2026 10:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/projects/the-weather-in-troms%C3%B8/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Tromsø is a city in the Arctic Circle where seasons are defined more by light than by temperature. This data visualization project explores a full year of weather in Tromsø through a set of vector-based visualizations that are both scientifically accurate and visually expressive. Every visual element was designed to echo the natural phenomena it represents, making data not only readable, but experiential.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The work was completed in &lt;strong&gt;one week&lt;/strong&gt; using only &lt;strong&gt;Google Sheets&lt;/strong&gt; for data processing and &lt;strong&gt;Figma&lt;/strong&gt; for design.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
